# ## General ###

# Dependencies
# These folders contain all the downloaded libraries for your project.
# They can be very large and should always be re-installed using `npm install`.
/node_modules
/frontend/node_modules
/backend/node_modules

# Environment Variables
# These files contain sensitive information like API keys, database URIs,
# and email passwords. NEVER commit these to version control.
# It's a best practice to create a `.env.example` file that lists the
# required variables without their values.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ## Frontend Specific (Vite/React) ###

# Build output
/frontend/dist

# Vite cache
/frontend/.vite/

# Test coverage
/frontend/coverage

